beer.beer_description: We absolutely cannot curb our enthusiasm for this Hazy IPA. Is it the wacky antics of Pilsner malt and Flaked Wheat? Is it the hilarity of Citra, Motueka, Alani & El Dorado hops? Is it the seamless banter between notes of pineapple, lime, orange zest & white wine? We don’t know. But it’s prettyyyyy prettyyyy…pretty good.

beer.beer_name: Cascade Fresh - Hazy Fresh Hop IPA
beer.beer_description: Time to polish up those pint glasses. Cascade is the hop that put Yakima Valley hop fields in the international spotlight. And we pay tribute to this with Cascade Fresh, featuring 400lbs of freshly harvested Cascade hops from CLS Farms in Moxee, WA. Brewed in collaboration with Vancouver, WA’s 3 locationed tap houses, TAPS! Look for mouthwatering notes of watermelon and citrus along with subtle notes of iced tea. This fresh-hopped beer will leave you feeling oh so fresh and so clean.

beer.beer_description: It’s the most wonderful time of the year…for hops and you too! Our 8th annual fresh hop collaboration with Moxee, WA’s C.L.S. Farms is made with a generous Wet Hopping of fresh Centennial hops. You’ll find fresh notes of lemongrass, honeydew melon, lemon and lime citrus. There is nothing quite like that first fresh hop beer of the year!

items.badge_description: You may not be able to see through the haze, but that juicy, hoppy goodness goes down smooth. What started as a trend is here to stay. That's 365 different beers with the style of IPA - New England / Hazy, Pale Ale - New England / Hazy, IPA - Milkshake, or Pale Ale - Milkshake. Try 5 more for Level 74!

beer.beer_description: Bobby, do you know what it takes to brew the perfect beer for Summer? Of course not, so let me tell ya, son. You’ve got to start with a good clean base malt. Think of it as the foundation just as propane is the foundation for any good barbecue. Next, ya gotta use hops and hopping accessories. Hops like Comet, Moutere & Triumph will produce bold notes of tangelo, grapefruit and lime zest. What you end up with is a pale and exceptionally drinkable ale. It’s a dang ‘ol Summer smasher, I tell you what, son.

beer.beer_name: All Terrain Hazy IPA collab w/ Barrel Mountain Brewing
beer.beer_description: Time for another adventure of the senses with our friends down south at Barrel Mountain Brewing! This beer takes the back roads and goes All Terrain through the pineapple groves, the passionfruit forests and the lime orchards thanks to Mosaic, Galaxy & El Dorado hops we made it with. Perfect for whatever the day brings, whether it’s riding the rapids or the trails, this hazy IPA is an adventure in itself and ready for any adventure you take it along for!

It might be hard for a frog, but it's Easy Being Green for this Fresh Hop Hazy IPA. Featuring over half a ton of fresh Cascade hops from CLS Farms on top of Azacca and Chinook hops. This IPA is a song in and of itself with flavors of watermelon & green tea and aromas of a green garden with a touch of honeydew melon. It's green, and it'll do fine. It's beautiful and I think it's what we all want to be.

When the sun is shining bright and the heat index is off the charts we know it’s time for a nice easy-drinking stout. Outdoor Stout is dark but light-bodied and perfect now, or any time of year. Like an iced-coffee with notes of chocolate and subtle cherry courtesy of pilsner malt, flaked oats & de-bittered black malts and the subtle hop addition of UK Goldings. Now is the time to enjoy the great Outdoors.

We made this beer with 100% Centennial hops gown by our friends at C.L.S. Farms in Moxee, Washington and went all out using 20lb per barrel, 600lb total, all in the whirlpool for an over saturated resinous hop character! No pellets or kilned hops were used in the brewing process. Fresh hop beers bring some of the most unique hop flavors of the year and can only be made in the late summer during harvest. C.L.S. Farms produces some of the best hops in the nation and we are proud to partner with them to make this beer!

It’s Back! The original NW Hazy IPA in a PINK can is easy drinking and ALL Fluffed up with El Dorado, Citra & Mosaic hops! It pours like fresh-squeezed orange juice with aromas of ripe mango, peach and tangerine floating on a cloud out of the glass. Fluffy mango, orange & papaya hit the palate softly, as if landing on a pillow-top bed. Even though the hype behind Hazy IPAs continues, we know the hype is All Fluff.

Once there was All Fluff and we thought it was all the fluff we needed. But we quickly realized that people wanted more! So we gave them MORE and created Super Fluff. More Citra! More El Dorado! More Mosaic! More haze! More Fluff! More more more! More fluffy notes of pineapple, fresh squeezed OJ, strawberry and mango. This beer is limited so enjoy more while you can!

For the penultimate installment of our 2024 fresh hop season we brought 600 lbs of fresh Citra hops from Carpenter Ranches all the way to Tumwater and threw them in the lauter tun. And thus the freshest, fluffiest & haziest IPA in all the land is born, bursting with notes of mango, apricot and orange zest. So many fresh hops were harmed in the making of this beer, there oughta be a law.

Not sure what to expect in 2025?  Us either.  One thing we do know is that we can’t go wrong reaching for a hazy IPA.  And this Hazy IPA is no exception, loaded with Amarillo, Centennial & Simcoe hops for an old school meets new school clash of deliciousness.  Look through the haze for notes of ripe citrus, pine and smooth tropical fruit. Here’s to a new year and many more new beers!

Sweet sticky hop nectar has fallen from the bine with aromas of citrus, guava and stone fruit. Citra, El Dorado & Vic Secret hops combine for one smooth Double IPA. Rich fruity hop, apricot, mango, and citrus flavors abound. Not to be confused with the other “nectar" in a can.

It might be hard for a frog, but it's Easy Being Green for this Fresh Hop Hazy IPA. Featuring over half a ton of fresh Cascade hops from CLS Farms on top of Azacca and Chinook hops. This IPA is a song in and of itself with flavors of watermelon & green tea and aromas of a green garden with a touch of honeydew melon. It's green, and it'll do fine. It's beautiful and I think it's what we all want to be.

Voss IPA is brewed with a Norwegian yeast strain that is native to the region of Voss, Norway.  This yeast harmonizes with Waimea, Rakau and Vic Secret hops to create some crazy, crisp citrus and tropical fruit flavors including ripe pineapple; all complemented by a refreshing malt body. Skol!

Puzzling? Not really! It's just water, malt, yeast and most importantly, hops! Loaded with... you guessed it, Citra and Enigma at a 2:1 ratio. Enjoy big, bright aromas and flavors of tangerine, orange and lychee provided by Citra tied together with Enigma’s unique dank / herbal spice and tropical fruitiness. Just try and put these puzzle pieces together!

We might not be able to enjoy the striped, bright-colored and fruit-flavored gum of our youth. (RIP: Fruit Stripe Gum - 1960 - 2024) But we still long for those tropical and citrus fruit flavors. So much so that we made an IPA that does the same thing! We used the right combination of hops (for flavor that lasts) like El Dorado, Topaz, Centennial & Mosaic (for tropical fruity sweetness). Say hello to the only Hazy IPA that makes you think of cartoon zebras.

This West Coast Style IPA doesn’t shy away from the traditional bitterness of a true IPA while at the same time showcasing bold tropical fruit character.  The beer starts off with a nose of ripe tropical fruit, including Pineapple and Papaya. Mango and nectarine follow through on the palate along with notes of cantaloupe and honeydew rounding it out.  Nothing is held back with the bright, medium body that allows the showcase of fruit character to shine through.  No fruit was harmed during the making of this beer because Hops the New Fruit!

Our biannual version of a classic West Coast IPA. Big notes of fresh pine and crushed citrus get us all nostalgic about the glory days of IPA, and this beer delivers on that. The old-meets-new malt bill of  Pilsner and Munich malts adds just a touch of sweetness to balance that old school grapefruit & pine-like bitterness from Amarillo, Centennial & Simcoe hops. A modern take on a classic IPA that keeps you wanting to drink on!

Made exclusively with hops and malt from Washington State! Fresh Centennial hop cones from CLS Farms meet Yakima grown Centennial and Chinook hops and Skagit Valley Malting’s Fritz Ale malt. Look for big green floral notes and lemon-lime. There is nothing like that first fresh hop of the year!

It’s that time of the year for Citrus Drop Triple IPA. Huge fruit character, but no actual fruit was harmed in the making of this big ol’ IPA, just a bunch of citrus loaded hops! This year we dropped tons of Eclipse, Comet, Chinook and Citra in for blasts of citrus, pine, lemon/lime and a touch of mango. It’s big. And juicy. And oh soooooo smooth.

beer.beer_name: These Pretzels Are Making Me Thirsty!
beer.beer_description: It’s that time of year to break out the pretzels again! And we all know what pretzels do…This Festbier is the perfect answer to your thirst!  Brewed with a single decoction of Montana Craft Malt PIlsner, Vienna & Munich Light malts along with Spalter Select and Czech Saaz hops.This lager highlights the traditional clean malty body while showcasing herbal and citrus notes. Sporting your dirndl or lederhosen this Festbier up by the litre or 16oz can. Prost!

We made 9thCoud for our good friends at Beer Authority and Berk! The beer is a hazy tweener, more a NEIPA but still with a dry North West soul. Look forward to our extravagant use of Waimea, Eldorado and Citra hops softly enveloped in the fluffiest jammies oats, wheat and Pils malts can afford.

Our Mexican-inspired lager is easy drinking and perfect for any day in the PNW. Golden hued with a fluffy white head this one goes down with a crisp, thirst-quenching ahhhhhh. Pilsner, Vienna and flaked corn meld with the lime tinged hop stylings of Wakatu leaving you saying uno mas!

In the PNW the Haze belongs in our IPAs not in our skies. We hopped this cloudy brew with Waimea, Simcoe & Moutere on a base of Pilsner & Munich malts with Flaked Oats. Look for notes of stone fruity plums and apricots with a hint of pineapple and mango. You might not be able to see through this beer but it's nice to be able to see across town this time of year.

For "Juice of Champions" DIPA we went for maximum juice effect to deliver the highest juice units possible! Though no fruit was harmed in the making ​of this beer, but plenty of Citra and Amarillo were! Big and bright with alternating layers of peaches, melons, & citrus with a soft, pillowy, pulp free mouthfeel thanks to a small amount of flaked corn and wheat; sorry not fruits!
***Warning, due to some confusion in the market with "Juice Cleanse" IPA, "Juice of Champions" is a beer​ not a ​dietary food supplement​ nor in fact a juicer itself.***

How do you pack a basket full of fruit flavor into every pint of What the Fruit IPA? Dump in a bunch of fruit purées? Not a chance! We loaded a bunch of fruity El Dorado, Topaz & Rakau hops in and fermented this IPA with Juice yeast. And then we dry-hopped with even more of the same hops for even more fruity goodness. The aroma has big notes of tropical and citrus fruits while each sip is filled with pineapple, orange, mango, strawberry and lime notes. Like a basket of fruit in a pint of beer.

We’ve got a big pile of hops left over from our hop contracts; better make some more IPA. This year's Over Contracted release features New Zealand favorites Moutere & Motueka hops, bringing zippy grapefruit and lime notes. Along with Washington’s own Amarillo & El Dorado hops adding a touch of tropical fruit like pineapple. When life hands you hops, brew IPA.

Break out the poinsettias ‘cause we’ve got some Celebrating to do! We brought in a fresh bale of whole leaf El Dorado hops from our friends at CLS Farms and packed this beer with all of its hoppy goodness. This labor of love teems with notes of watermelon, pear, light citrus and herbal hop flowers. Finally, an IPA with fresh-kilned hops. Why didn’t somebody think of this first?

Triplecicle is 3 IPAs in one! Heavily dry-hopped with citrus-forward Citra, Comet and Chinook hops went into this, as well as whole Madagascar vanilla beans, and finished with citrus terpenes to make a rich and orange-creamy finish. If you’re a fan of Creamcicles, you know what we’re talking about.

Our original on a classic German Pilsner. OG Pils (as we like to call it) is step-mashed with a blend of Pilsner malts, yielding rich malt character and is married with additions of Czech Saaz & Tetnanger for a light and spicy hop presence. Perfect for sipping indoors or outside this time of year. Prost!

Do you ever find yourself blasting Judas Priest and daydreaming about what an IPA would taste like if you fermented it at 100+ degrees using a Norwegian yeast and then dry-hopped it with unholy amounts of El Dorado, Galaxy, Topaz and Citra hops? Oh, just me?! Well try this on for size: MASSIVE, face-melting riffs of pineapple, tangerine, orange and even a smidge of ripe melon screaming into the ears of your tongue. Crank up the British Steel and chug some Norse Gold!

That's it!  Nothing more, nothing less, just two of our favorite hops in a naked duet.  Meant to show off the two hottest hops in the last two decades. Look for it, candied pine and citrus, mild bitterness and an almost non existent malt softness.
